{{Quote|You can leave any messages with the night bartender at the Dona Laza tapcafe.|[[Aves]], to [[Wedge Antilles/Legends|Wedge Antilles]]|<ref name="TLC" />}}
The '''Dona Laza''' was a [[Tapcafe/Legends|tapcafe]] situated on a [[Unidentified planet (Dona Laza)|planet]]<ref name="TLC" /> located in the [[Dona Laza sector/Legends|Dona Laza sector]] of the [[Expansion Region/Legends|Expansion Region]].<ref name="Planetnamia">{{Planetnamia|other=the Dona Laza [[Tapcafe/Legends|tapcafe]]|system=[[Dona Laza system/Legends|Dona Laza system]]|legends=1}}</ref><ref name="EAOC">{{SW|url=news/star-wars-the-essential-atlas-online-companion|text=''Star Wars: The Essential Atlas'' Online Companion|int=Star Wars: The Essential Atlas Online Companion}} &mdash; Based on corresponding data for [[Dona Laza system/Legends|Dona Laza system]]</ref>

==History==
{{Quote|Popular place tonight.''"<br />"''It's their turn at the floating Boga Minawk tournament. You wouldn't believe how crazy they go for the game around here.|[[Shada D'ukal]] and [[Mazzic]]|<ref name="SofP">''[[Specter of the Past]]''</ref>}}
During the [[Thrawn campaign]] of [[9 ABY/Legends|9 ABY]], [[Aves]], a member of [[Talon Karrde]]'s [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggling]] [[Car'das/Legends|organization]], told the [[New Republic pilot/Legends|New Republic pilot]] [[Wedge Antilles/Legends|Wedge Antilles]] that any messages left with the Dona Laza's [[Local day/Legends|night]] [[Bartender/Legends|bartender]] would reach him.<ref name="TLC" />

During the [[Caamas Document Crisis]] of [[19 ABY/Legends|19 ABY]], the smuggler [[Mazzic]], along with [[Shada D'ukal]], [[Griv]] and [[Cromf]], went to the Dona Laza [[Tapcafe/Legends|tapcafe]] in order to catch [[Lak Jit]], an [[Information broker/Legends|information broker]] who was selling information on a [[Bothan/Legends|Bothan]] involvement in the [[Caamas Firestorm|destruction]] of [[Caamas/Legends|Caamas]].<ref name="SofP" />

At the [[Time/Legends|time]], the establishment was frequented by a large number of [[Boga Minawk]] enthusiasts.<ref name="SofP" />

